# mkdocs-cdoc

![Claude](https://img.shields.io/badge/Claude-D97757?style=for-the-badge&logo=claude&logoColor=white)

[![CI](https://github.com/pawelsikora/mkdocs-cdoc/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/pawelsikora/mkdocs-cdoc/actions/workflows/ci.yml)
[![Docs](https://github.com/pawelsikora/mkdocs-cdoc/actions/workflows/docs.yml/badge.svg)](https://pawelsikora.github.io/mkdocs-cdoc/)
[![Python](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/mkdocs-cdoc)](https://pypi.org/project/mkdocs-cdoc/)
[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/mkdocs-cdoc)](https://pypi.org/project/mkdocs-cdoc/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/pawelsikora/mkdocs-cdoc)](LICENSE)
[![MkDocs](https://img.shields.io/badge/MkDocs-plugin-blue)](https://www.mkdocs.org/)
[![Discord](https://img.shields.io/discord/1474618001558081586?logo=discord&label=Discord&color=5865F2)](https://discord.gg/dqadWt5p4g)

**Generate browsable API documentation from C/C++ source comments directly in MkDocs** — with cross-referencing, symbol indexing, and first-class support for [IGT GPU Tools](https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/igt-gpu-tools) test catalogs.

📖 **[Full Documentation](https://pawelsikora.github.io/mkdocs-cdoc/)** · 🎯 **[Live Example](https://pawelsikora.github.io/mkdocs-cdoc/example-site/)**

---

## Features

- **Autodoc from C/C++ sources** — scans source trees, extracts `/** ... */` doc comments, generates per-file pages with function signatures, parameter tables, and struct/enum member listings
- **Cross-reference everything** — `:func:`, `:struct:`, `:file:`, backtick auto-linking across generated pages and hand-written Markdown
- **Multiple source groups** — separate nav sections for libraries, drivers, tests, each with their own A–Z index and overview
- **IGT test catalog** — parses `TEST:` / `SUBTEST:` structured comments and `igt_subtest()` / `igt_describe()` macros to build test catalogs with metadata tables and "By Category" / "By Functionality" index pages
- **gtk-doc migration** — converts `#TypeName`, `function()`, `%CONSTANT`, `@param` markup, plus a CLI for batch conversion
- **Clang + regex** — uses libclang when available, falls back to regex so it works everywhere

## Quick start

```bash
pip install mkdocs-cdoc
```

Minimal `mkdocs.yml`:

```yaml
plugins:
  - cdoc:
      source_root: src/
```

Multi-source with IGT test support:

```yaml
plugins:
  - cdoc:
      project_name: My Project
      version_file: meson.build

      sources:
        - root: lib
          nav_title: Core API
          output_dir: api/lib

        - root: tests
          nav_title: Tests
          output_dir: api/tests
          extensions: [".c"]
          igt:
            group_by: [category, mega_feature, sub_category, functionality]

      convert_rst: true
      convert_gtkdoc: true
```

